<TITLE> RAB arrests Delwar's son Paban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 30 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion arrested Akhter Hamid Paban, son of embattled BNP leader Khandaker Delwar Hossain, Tuesday night, hours after a Dhaka court issued an arrest warrant. Major Mahmud Hossain of RAB-4 confirmed the news to bdnews24.com. "Paban was arrested at Japan Garden City in Mohammadpur shortly after 9pm," he said. The Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka Tuesday issued the order to arrest Paban in a carjacking case. According to case details, Paban's associates on October 13, 2005 stole a car of businessman Kazi Mizanur Rahman, which was parked in front of Amin Court in Motijheel. Security forces retrieved the car and arrested him. A case was filed with Motijheel Police Station. Paban received bail from the High Court in the case on December 28, 2006. bd
